  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We study uniform Sobolev inequalities for the second order differential operators <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> of non-elliptic type. For <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>d</mi><mo>≥</mo><mn>3</mn></math> we prove that the Sobolev type estimate <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">‖</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy="false">‖</mo></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></msub><mo>≤</mo><mi>C</mi><msub><mrow><mo stretchy="false">‖</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy="false">‖</mo></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msup><mrow><mi mathvariant="double-struck">R</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></msub></math> holds with C independent of the first order and the constant terms of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> if and only if <math altimg="si4.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>d</mi></math> and <math altimg="si5.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac></math> . We also obtain restricted weak type endpoint estimates for the critical <math altimg="si6.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>p</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>q</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mi>d</mi></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mfrac><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> , <math altimg="si7.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>d</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mi>d</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> . As a consequence, the result extends the class of functions for which the unique continuation for the inequality <math altimg="si560.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><mi>P</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>D</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><mo>≤</mo><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><mi>V</mi><mi>u</mi><mo stretchy="false">|</mo></math> holds.</subfield>
